block.documentation:
The Logistics & Storage Subsystem plays a vital role in managing the flow of raw materials and finished products within the AOMS, ensuring continuous manufacturing operations and efficient handling of resources. Material Storage Units house the ZBLAN preforms used in fiber production, while Product Storage Units securely store the finished ZBLAN fibers until they are ready for transport. The subsystem is equipped with Material Handling Robotics, which automate the transfer of materials between storage areas and the manufacturing subsystem, enabling seamless production without human involvement.
Additionally, the subsystem is integrated with a Docking Ring, which allows the AOMS to dock with resupply capsules. This feature is essential for receiving new materials and offloading finished products to Earth. The Inventory Management CSC oversees stock levels, automatically tracking the quantities of raw materials and finished fibers. This software ensures efficient resource management by scheduling resupply missions as needed and maintaining an up-to-date inventory to prevent shortages that could interrupt production.
